From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ASRock X570D4I-2T OpenBMC port <nbatkins@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 13 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] ast2500: actively enable Super-I/O + iLPC2AHB for SUPERIO

isolate_bmc() disables the AST2500 LPC Super-I/O decode (SCU70 bit20)
and the iLPC2AHB bridge (LPC HICRB bit6). On the ASRock Rack X570D4I-2T
the host BIOS Redfish Host Interface driver uses the Super-I/O at host
I/O 0x4E/0x4F, logical device 0x0D = the iLPC2AHB bridge, to read
AST2500 GPIO E4 (AHB 0x1E780020 bit4) as a "BMC ready" gate before
bringing up the host Redfish-over-USB network interface. With the bridge
disabled that read fails and the host never connects.

CONFIG_ASPEED_ENABLE_SUPERIO only stops isolate_bmc() from re-asserting
the SCU70 disable strap, but the strap/reset DEFAULT on this board leaves
both the Super-I/O decode and the iLPC2AHB disabled, so "not disabling"
is not enough -- the disable bits must be actively CLEARED. Do that when
CONFIG_ASPEED_ENABLE_SUPERIO is set: clear SCU70 bit20 via the SCU7C
strap-clear register (HW_STRAP1 + 0xc; the strap register is write-1-set
so a plain RMW cannot clear it) and clear HICRB bit6 with a normal RMW.
The HICRB write was previously unconditional; it is now part of the
disable path taken only when SUPERIO is not enabled. Other isolations
(P2A/PCIe, debug UART, X-DMA/GFX, FWH) are untouched.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [board-specific configuration]
diff --git a/arch/arm/mach-aspeed/ast2500/board_common.c b/arch/arm/mach-aspeed/ast2500/board_common.c
index c63fe46..1eed0eb 100644
--- a/arch/arm/mach-aspeed/ast2500/board_common.c
+++ b/arch/arm/mach-aspeed/ast2500/board_common.c
@@ -36,15 +36,29 @@ static void isolate_bmc(void)
 	u32 val;
 
 	/* iLPC2AHB */
-#if !defined(CONFIG_ASPEED_ENABLE_SUPERIO)
+#if defined(CONFIG_ASPEED_ENABLE_SUPERIO)
+	/*
+	 * Actively ENABLE the Super-I/O decode + iLPC2AHB bridge for the host
+	 * Redfish Host Interface (RedfishHi reads BMC GPIOE4 via the iLPC2AHB as a
+	 * "BMC ready" gate). The strap/reset defaults leave both DISABLED, so the
+	 * disable bits must be CLEARED -- merely not re-setting them is not enough.
+	 * SCU70 bit20 is a hardware strap (write-1-set); clear it through the SCU7C
+	 * strap-clear register at HW_STRAP1 + 0xc. HICRB bit6 is a normal RMW.
+	 */
+	writel(SCU_HWSTRAP_LPC_SIO_DEC_DIS, ASPEED_HW_STRAP1 + 0xc);
+
+	val = readl(ASPEED_LPC_CTRL + AST_LPC_HICRB);
+	val &= ~LPC_HICRB_SIO_ILPC2AHB_DIS;
+	writel(val, ASPEED_LPC_CTRL + AST_LPC_HICRB);
+#else
 	val = readl(ASPEED_HW_STRAP1);
 	val |= SCU_HWSTRAP_LPC_SIO_DEC_DIS;
 	writel(val, ASPEED_HW_STRAP1);
-#endif
 
 	val = readl(ASPEED_LPC_CTRL + AST_LPC_HICRB);
 	val |= LPC_HICRB_SIO_ILPC2AHB_DIS;
 	writel(val, ASPEED_LPC_CTRL + AST_LPC_HICRB);
+#endif
 
 	/* P2A, PCIe BMC */
 	val = readl(ASPEED_PCIE_CONFIG_SET);
-- 
